%% This paper looks at the adaptation of solar energy in the build environment from an electronic engineering prospective. To be able to predict the future demand on the electricity grid, the authors try to find patterns in the spatial delusions of solar energy. The results are not really clear. The result of the analysis is a logistic regression table with parameters contributing to the possibility of a household buying PV. The biggest factor for forecasting the adaptation for PV is the annual income of the household. The second parameter is the numbers for PV panels in a radius of 100 meter around the house. So the presence of PV in the neighborhood increases the likelihood of a household to buy PV. The interesting thing is that the regression table also shows that the presence of PV in a radius of 250 meter around the house has a negative relation with the chance of the house having PV. This is a interesting fact that requires extra investigation and is a good reason for writing this thesis.  

